{"questionId":"21476","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The diagram shows the slope field for the differential equation</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>y</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mi>sin</mi><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>y</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>≤</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>≤</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>≤</mo><mi>y</mi><mo>≤</mo><mn>5</mn></math>.</p>\n<p>The graphs of the two solutions to the differential equation that pass through points <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>(</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>)</mo></math>&nbsp;and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>(</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>)</mo></math> are shown.</p>\n<p><img style=\"display:block;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;\" src=\"__IMG__/0ccefbb4807f89d2ec735990feabfe6846e8b1c2.png\"></p>\n<p>For the two solutions given, the local minimum points lie on the straight line <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>L</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Find the equation of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>L</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></math>, giving your answer in the form <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>m</mi><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>c</mi></math>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>sin</mi><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>y</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math>&nbsp;<em><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>⇒</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math>&nbsp;<em><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; (M1)</strong></em></p>\n